description: Our new editrix ushers in a flurry of fabulous firsts in Gearhearts history! Our first returning Brass Belle, gorgeous German MADemoiselle Meli, is back with new eye-popping photographs. Behold the free-spirited, sexy watercolors of our first Swedish illustrator, Jennie Gyllblad. Feast on our first foray into the Victorian serial story tradition, with part one of a captivating tripartite tale by Melanie Fletcher. Climb on board the zeppelin for espionage, love, mad science, and, of course, steampunk beauties!
An unnumbered ashcan that was "rediscovered" in around 2010

All college students Jayce, Hawk, Alice, and Gina want to do is kick back and relax when they happen to land some downtime. And now that Hawk's latest creation, the sweet but dangerously superpowered android Eve, is finally starting to settle in with her motley crew of roommates, it looks like they'll actually get that chance! But a simple trip to the mall goes horribly awry, and when Eve goes haywire it's up to her newfound friends to calm her down, or shut her down!

Includes over 150 comics originally posted on applegeeks.com during 2005 and 2006, plus creator commentary, pinup galleries, and more!

Applegeeks.com web traffic averages forty thousand unique visitors per day and over 2.5 million page views per month.
name: Weird Science

description: Brush up on your art fundamentals with the Riverdale gang! Archie, Betty, Veronica, Chuck and the gang are painting the town red -- literally! Check out some of Riverdale's most colorful characters expressing themselves through art. They'll try their hand at sculpture, painting, drawing, and more in 50 pages of fun! Get ready --these stories are so funny they could make Mona Lisa laugh!
name: Picture Perfect!

description: Brains is invited to partake in a seminary where all the smart people of the world will be gathered. At the end however, he has disappeared. The only clue is his hat, laying on the street. Detective Armando comes into action and brings Dweezil and Lisa to a chinese take away restaurant. But if they will find Brains there, remains the question. Where is that boy? Maybe the prized doves of dovemilker Dweezil can find him! Again an incredible exciting story with a surprising end!
name: De Meeneemchinees

deck: Collecting/re-printing the first three "chapters" that were published last year by Image.
description:
In 1998's Legends (edited by Robert Silverberg) George R. R. Martin released a novella set in his Westeros (Game of Thrones) world. Last year Image Comics started to retell that story in graphic novel/comic book format, but now Devil's Due Publishing and DBPro (which would later become Dabel Brothers and be absorbed by Marvel) takes up that tale.

Before starting new issues to finish this tale, here is a single collected issue of the three Image books...
name: Chapters 1-3
